SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04570627
Version: 1

HPSBMU03259 rev.1 - HP Version Control Repository Manager running OpenSSL on
Linux and Windows, Remote Disclosure of Information

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2015-03-09
Last Updated: 2015-03-09

Potential Security Impact: Disclosure of information

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with the HP Version
Control Repository Manager running OpenSSL on Linux and Windows. This
vulnerability is the SSLv3 vulnerability known as "Padding Oracle on
Downgraded Legacy Encryption" or "POODLE", which could be exploited remotely
to allow disclosure of information.

References:

CVE-2014-3566
CVE-2014-5139
SSRT101922

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP Version Control Repository Manager prior to version 7.4.1

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2014-3566    (AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:P/I:N/A:N)       4.3
CVE-2014-5139    (AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:N/I:N/A:P)       4.3
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HP has provided an updated version of the HP Version Control Repository
Manager to address these vulnerabilities. HP Version Control Repository
Manager v7.4.1 is available at the following Software Depot download
location:

Windows VCRM 7.4.1 :

http://www.hp.com/swpublishing/MTX-766934f4856b406d82876f5cb3

ftp://ftp.hp.com/pub/softlib2/software1/sc-windows/p283849675/v101784

